Love a good 📷 play sesh! Here are my ⭐️5 TIPS FOR A DIY BRANDING SHOOT 📸:

1. Plan & Prep: ✏️ Have a goal for the photo(s) you want to capture. Colors, mood, tone, use online. Cropping!? Schedule a half day to get the pics done from makeup to editing!
2. Choose a ✨Well Lit Location. ✨Yes, anywhere from your bedroom, office, garage, kitchen… The key is to find the ⚡️magical⚡️ lighting. Don’t waste time on studio lighting (unless u are a pro). You want white, glossy, bright, glowy sun light. Cloudy days with BIG glow are my faves. Stay away from sunbeams or harsh shadows. Pro-tip: go ALL WHITE on backgrounds and even flooring. White reflects light! You can buy a @vflatworld or even use poster board to cover up wood floors or busy walls. With the tech these days, erasing a clean background and adding any color background in editing! Re: @canva background remover rocks.
3. Style + Mood. 👗Choose your wardrobe (at least 3 looks, no more than 6.) And style your hair and makeup in a natural way, while turning colors up a notch. Brighter blush, lips, eyes… poofier hair, brighter wardrobe colors. Don’t be afraid of COLOR here. Pro tip: I 🤍 white shirts, but on camera they fall flat. Go for colors that u know compliment your skin and do one ALL BLACK look. It’s fun to play w poses and edit! If u hate black, do another one-color outfit. Try more snug tops so you can show off your gestures!
4. EQUIPMENT! 📷 obvi a fancy camera is best. Don’t do iPhones unless u have to - u won’t get a truly professional look. You can rent cameras @borrowlenses - cool! Or invest 💰📷. I use a @canonusa R6 w a 50mm for portraits. get a good tripod. And a mini remote! I use the 2 second delay setting and snap w remote in hand. It’s easy to conceal! For editing, I use Lightroom @adobe and Canva for graphics and resizing.
5. Practice! 👏Don’t expect to get your best photos the first shoot. You will learn SO MUCH about your body, personality, face, expressions, energy and more when you do these photo shoots.

GO PRO: A few times u must shoot with PROS! These are great for outdoor locations + EASE + EDUCATION! Plus you get a new L👀K using a different artist!

+ HAVE FUN 🤩 #photography #entrepreneur

Hi Friends! Let’s get reacquainted! 👋🏻 
1️⃣ I’m Kathy! I am a writer, recipe developer & photographer. On my blog, HealthyHappyLife.com, I share plant-based recipes, travel, life & some vegan glam. I’ve worked with dozens of global brands on plant-based content collabs. 💃🏼
2️⃣ I’ve authored two cookbooks, 365 Vegan Smoothies & Healthy Happy Vegan Kitchen. 📚 
3️⃣ California-girl, I adore farmer’s markets, wide beaches, pink sunsets & easy parking.🌴 4️⃣ Vegan for 20 years. For the animals. Vegan is not a diet. It is a choice your heart makes. 🌱
5️⃣ Career highlight: Spotting my cookbook in a Florence, Italy bookstore - translated in Italian.👀 6️⃣ I’m an introvert who still loves a good time! Or just getting glammed up to take tons of pics. 📸 
7️⃣ My travel happy place: the hotel spa after a day of 👟 exploring. 🧖🏼‍♀️
8️⃣ I created FindingVegan.com to foster veg inspo, tools + community! 🌱 follow: @findingvegan 
9️⃣ Growing up I had an eating disorder. I never thought I would live a “normal & healthy” life, but here I am! I attribute so much healing to my plant-based life. 🌱🥰 1️⃣0️⃣ I love traveling to movie / TV show filming locations! ✨✈️ 
1️⃣1️⃣ Fave GOT characters: Jamie, Cersei, Arya. 🐉  1️⃣1️⃣ Team Britney. My very first website was a Britney Spears fan blog (2006) that got me featured on TMZ, twice. I will teach u the “Oops” music video dance, anytime. 🎶 🧑‍🚀 🎤 
1️⃣3️⃣ Infertility / IVF warrior. The best pandemic present: my daughter. 🤱🏼
1️⃣4️⃣ Fave movie: Titanic. I will forever be 16, sobbing in a dark theater to My Heart Will Go on. 🚢 
1️⃣5️⃣ I have my BS in nutrition & health promotion from American University in DC. 
I graduated from UCLA’s screenwriting certificate program.✏️ 1️⃣6️⃣ Kitty lover: Sochi & Mr. White.🐱🐱
1️⃣7️⃣ Tennis is my fave sport to watch & play. 🎾 
1️⃣8️⃣ Living in NYC inspired me to start my blog. 🏙️
1️⃣9️⃣ Signature recipe: my Sweet Potato Veggie Burgers with avocado. 

🤍 so glad u are here! Maybe we share goals or a goofy sense of fun or adventure - a mindset for compassion, wellness, or creativity - whatever it is, let’s keep chatting, friend!
